<p>I want to know how to get number of radio buttons by name in AngularJS using a directive. </p>  <pre><code>&lt;label ng-repeat="elements in [1,2,3,4,5,6,7]"&gt;       &lt;input type="radio" name="phone" ng-model="phone" value="example"&gt;  &lt;/label&gt;  &lt;!--Directive by name (phone), number of radio buttons is 7--&gt;  &lt;label ng-repeat="elements in [1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9]"&gt;       &lt;input type="radio" name="OS" ng-model="OS" value="example"&gt;  &lt;/label&gt;  &lt;!--Directive by name (OS), number of radio buttons is 9--&gt; </code></pre>